<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>Astro Blog Review Prototype</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A small prototype for evaluating whether Astro can replace Ghost's blogging/content functionality."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>Astro Blog Review Prototype</h1>

      <p>
        This prototype evaluates whether Astro can replace Ghost's blogging and
        content functionality for this website.
      </p>

      <nav>
        <a href="/blog">Blog</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
      </nav>

      <h2>Tested so far</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Markdown posts</li>
        <li>MDX posts with Astro components</li>
        <li>Typed frontmatter via Content Collections</li>
        <li>Blog index route</li>
        <li>Dynamic blog post routes</li>
        <li>Tag routes</li>
        <li>Draft filtering</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Current conclusion</h2>

      <p>
        Astro works well for file-based blogging and static content rendering.
        It does not provide a built-in Ghost-like content admin by itself.
      </p>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>